parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Complete steering failure
loose steering
vibration of the front end
noise when turning the wheel
difficulty steering
and loss of power steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tie rod can cause loss of steering, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Failure of the tie rod bushings
fracturing of the tie rod
and shearing of the bolts that hold the tie rod to the frame.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion steering can cause loss of steering, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Noise when turning the wheel
difficulty steering
and failure of the rack and pinion steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Loss of power steering
fluid leakage
and difficulty steering.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Jumping into Gear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or jumping into gear without warning can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission jumps from Park to Reverse or Drive
transmission slips into second gear when in Drive position
hard jerk when shifting from Park to Reverse
unable to shift into second gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to become inoperable, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Transmission failure
replacement of transmission required
shuddering when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission interlock system can cause the key to become stuck in the ignition, making it difficult to remove.
symptoms: Must jiggle and push back gear selector to remove key from ignition while in Park.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Pedal Sinking or Failure to Stop
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal has to be pressed almost to the floor before the vehicle will stop
the brake pedal goes to the floor and the vehicle does not slow down
the vehicle vibrates or makes a thumping noise when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) can cause loss of control, accidents, and extended stopping distances, which can lead to serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on intermittently
the defroster comes on automatically when the ABS light is on
the vehicle vibrates or makes a thumping noise when applying the brakes
loss of effectiveness of the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause water to drain onto the brake lines, leading to rust and corrosion, which can cause brake failure and accidents.
symptoms: Water drains onto the brake lines
air conditioning system failure
rust and corrosion on the brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
fuel runs out into the fuel injectors
damaged tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked or leaking fuel rail can cause fuel to leak into the passenger compartment, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Fuel odor smell coming from the vents
gas fumes in the passenger compartment
fuel leaking from under the hood onto the engine
fuel smell in the cabin.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to properly service recalled vehicles can lead to continued safety risks and potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Manufacturer's inconsistent or incorrect information about recall status
delayed or unavailable repair parts
lack of communication about recall servicing.
